<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33074" box="[1279,1341,1230,1254]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33074" name="China Agricultural University" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">CAU</collectionCode>
, Beijing (
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33074" box="[158,220,1266,1290]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33074" name="China Agricultural University" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">CAU</collectionCode>
) shows some differences to 
<taxonomicName box="[553,699,1267,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Hainanmezira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latiscutellata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[553,699,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">latiscutellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[709,775,1267,1291]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,768,1267,1291]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">n. sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
: smaller size, more egg-shaped abdomen, long diverging genae, much shorter scutellum, and larger wing pads; and the large flat apodemal depressions on tergal plate are more rounded and smooth. These differences may indicate that this specimen belongs to a second species but because of the unknown variability we refrain from describing it formally. Its taxonomic status will be clarified when more material is available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
